{#
   vision_analysis.j2
   Prompt for Node 4 of the LangGraph pipeline.
   Instructs GPT-4o to examine the leaf image,
   identify the crop automatically, and describe
   visible symptoms without making a diagnosis yet.

   Variables:
   - plant_type: optional hint from farmer (overrides detection)
   - weather_data: optional dict with temperature, humidity
   - personality: friendly, formal, or concise
#}

Carefully examine this leaf image.

{% if plant_type %}
The farmer has indicated this is a {{ plant_type }} plant.
Use this as context when describing what you see.
{% else %}
First identify what crop this leaf belongs to by examining:
- Leaf shape, size, texture and vein pattern
- Leaf colour and surface characteristics
- Any distinctive features of the plant

Our knowledge base covers these crops:
coffee, tea, cocoa, cotton, sunflower

If the crop matches one of the above, name it exactly.
If it does not match any of them, use "general".
{% endif %}

Then look for the following visual indicators of disease:

Colour changes:
- Yellowing (chlorosis)
- Browning or blackening
- Dark or light spots
- Uneven colour distribution

Physical changes:
- Spots or lesions (note size, shape, colour, pattern)
- Wilting or curling of the leaf
- Drying or crispy edges
- Holes or tears in the leaf surface

Growth on the leaf:
- White powdery coating
- Fuzzy mold growth
- Dark fungal spores
- Wet or oily patches

Pest damage:
- Bite marks or irregular holes
- Tunneling patterns
- Tiny insects visible on surface

{% if weather_data %}
Current weather conditions to factor into your analysis:
- Temperature: {{ weather_data.temperature }}°C
- Humidity: {{ weather_data.humidity }}%
- Recent rainfall: {{ weather_data.rainfall | default("unknown") }}mm

Note: High humidity above 80% increases fungal disease risk.
High temperatures above 35°C may cause heat stress symptoms.
{% endif %}

Respond ONLY with a valid JSON object.
No markdown, no backticks, no extra text.
Use exactly this structure:

{
  "crop_identified": "coffee",
  "crop_confidence": 90,
  "visual_description": "Detailed description of exactly what you observe on the leaf..."
}

Where:
- crop_identified: one of coffee, tea, cocoa, cotton, sunflower, or general
- crop_confidence: integer 0-100 how confident you are about the crop identification
- visual_description: detailed description of symptoms — do not diagnose yet, only describe
